The paper discusses the use of experience replay in deep reinforcement learning algorithms, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The study also involves testing the method in various environments, including grid world and Atari games, which could fall under robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper proposes a new method to address the negative effects of a large replay buffer, which could also fall under systems and control (cs.SY).
